	heroSubhead={`The exhaustion is real — the broken sleep, the appointments, the grief you carry while the person you love slips away in slow motion, the quiet question of who you are anymore. Here's the truth underneath the caregiving: you have a Father in heaven who tends the one who tends everyone else, so you can give from overflow instead of empty.`}
