	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you're caring for an aging parent, a sick spouse, or a child who needs you around the clock, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> These Bible verses for caregivers meet you where the weariness lives — the burnout, the isolation, the guilt that you're never doing enough, the grief that begins long before the goodbye. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for caregivers," "scripture for caring for aging parents," or "bible verses for caregiver strength" — the answer starts in one place: while you carry others through their hardest days, there is a Father carrying you.`}
	keyTakeaway={`You are not running on your own strength, and you were never meant to. You are the Father's beloved child — not just the dependable one, the strong one, the one everyone leans on. He tends the caregiver so the caregiver can keep giving, and He will carry you the whole way through.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight family caregivers carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel exhausted, invisible, guilty for needing a break, or like you've slowly lost yourself inside someone else's needs, you are not failing and you are not alone. Tens of millions of family caregivers carry the same weight — and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
