		{ ref: `Isaiah 40:31`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 40, text: `Those who hope in your Father will renew their strength; they will soar on wings like eagles, run and not grow weary, walk and not faint.`, note: `When your tank is empty, your Father is the source of strength that doesn't run dry.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 12:9`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 12, text: `My grace is enough for you, for My power is made perfect in weakness. So I will boast all the more gladly in my weaknesses, that the power of my Father may rest on me.`, note: `You don't have to be strong enough — your Father's strength shows up most clearly where yours runs out.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 68:19`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 68, text: `Praise be to your Father, who daily bears our burdens — the God who is our salvation.`, note: `Every single day, your Father carries the load you carry — you are not bearing it alone.` },
		{ ref: `1 Timothy 5:4`, slug: `1-timothy`, ch: 5, text: `If anyone has aging parents or grandparents, let them first learn to show godliness toward their own family and to repay their parents, for this is pleasing in the sight of your Father.`, note: `Caring for your aging parents is not a burden God overlooks — it is a holy work that delights your Father.` },
