	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for caregivers?`, answer: `Matthew 11:28-30 (come to Me and rest), Galatians 6:9 (do not grow weary in doing good), Isaiah 40:31 (renew their strength), 2 Corinthians 12:9 (My grace is enough, power in weakness), Psalm 68:19 (God daily bears our burdens), Isaiah 46:4 (I will carry you), and Matthew 25:40 (whatever you did for the least of these) all speak straight to what caregivers carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about caring for aging parents?`, answer: `The Bible treats caring for aging parents as a sacred duty and a way of honoring them. 1 Timothy 5:4 says those who care for their parents do what is 'pleasing in the sight of God,' and Exodus 20:12 commands us to honor our father and mother. Far from a burden God overlooks, it is holy work He sees and delights in. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals the God behind those passages as a Father who carries you as you care for them — read it free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a Bible verse for caregiver strength or burnout?`, answer: `Yes. Isaiah 40:31 promises that those who hope in the Lord will renew their strength and not grow weary, and 2 Corinthians 12:9 says God's grace is enough and His power is made perfect in weakness. Matthew 11:28 is the gentlest word for burnout: 'Come to Me, all you who are weary, and I will give you rest.' You can read or listen to all of them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about honoring your parents?`, answer: `Exodus 20:12 — 'Honor your father and your mother' — is one of the Ten Commandments, and the New Testament echoes it in 1 Timothy 5:4, where caring for aging parents is called pleasing to God. Honoring parents in their later years often looks like the daily, unglamorous work of caregiving, and Scripture treats it as a high calling. Meet the Father behind these verses in the Father's Heart Bible™, free with audio at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for caregivers?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — perfect for the hospital waiting room, the drive between appointments, or a sleepless night when you can't bring yourself to read but can still listen.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for caregivers?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of reading one more voice asking something of you, you meet the One who wants to fill you back up. For a caregiver pouring out day after day, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a loved child being tended, not just the strong one everyone leans on. Read it free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
